{{short description|Algebraic structure for which the fundamental theorem of algebra is true}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}
In [[mathematics]], a [[field (mathematics)|field]] {{math|''F''}} is '''algebraically closed''' if every [[Degree of a polynomial|non-constant polynomial]] in {{math|''F''[''x'']}} (the univariate [[polynomial ring]] with coefficients in {{math|''F''}}) has a [[Zero of a function|root]] in {{math|''F''}}.

